Supreme Court — Appellate Term, November, 1900.

Before Truax, P. J., Scott and Dugro, JJ.

Harry W. Bell, Respondent, v. Gabrielle Valente, Appellant. Appeal from a judgment and order of the General Term of the City Court of the city of New York, affirming a judgment in favor of plaintiff. I. Fraumthal (Joseph Fischer, of counsel), for appellant: L. B. Treadwell (R. W. Darling, of counsel), for respondent. Judgment and order affirmed, with costs.

No opinion.
